<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 17 at 7:50PM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Areas of fog this evening...
Areas of fog are being observed across portions of east central
New York and western New England, with patchy dense fog lowering
visibilities to a quarter of a mile in some locations. Fog is
expected to last through the night and dense fog may become more
widespread over the next several hours.
Motorists should exercise caution and be prepared for rapidly
changing visibilities. Slow down and allow extra distance between
vehicles. Also, use low beams in the fog.</description>
